5 institutions; and to provide for related matters.
6 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
7 Section 1. Code of Civil Procedure Art. 2415(B) is hereby amended and reenacted
8 and Code of Civil Procedure Art. 2415(C) and (D) are hereby enacted to read as follows:
9 Art. 2415. Delivery of property or payment of indebtedness to sheriff
10 * * *
11 B. Notwithstanding the requirements provided in Paragraph A of this
12 Article, if the garnishee is a federally insured financial institution and admits
13 in its answer that it has in its possession funds on deposit belonging to the
14 judgment debtor, and the garnishee has received no notice of opposition to the
15 garnishment, then, if the funds on deposit are one thousand dollars or less, the
16 garnishee may, without further court order, deliver the funds immediately to
17 the sheriff. Delivery or payment to the sheriff discharges the garnishee's
18 obligation to the judgment debtor to the extent of the delivery or payment to the
19 sheriff.
20 C. Notwithstanding the requirements provided in Paragraph A of this
21 Article, if the garnishee is a federally insured financial institution and admits
22 in its answer that it has in its possession funds on deposit belonging to the
23 judgment debtor, and the garnishee has received no notice of opposition to the
24 garnishment, and if the funds on deposit are greater than one thousand dollars,
25 then the garnishee may, upon waiting a period of thirty days after the filing of
26 its garnishment answer, and without further court order, deliver the funds on
27 deposit to the sheriff. Delivery or payment to the sheriff discharges the
